    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1864-12-26T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1864-12-26T00:00:00-05:00" n="42" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d42">
                <head>
                    <persName type="from">Mr. Burnley</persName> to <persName type="to">Mr. Seward</persName>
                </head>
                <p rend="center">[Memorandum.]</p>
                <p>Relative to the apprehended attempts of persons hostile to the United
                            States from Canada, Viscount Monck informs me that he has taken measures
                            for the prevention of such acts, by the establishment of a detective
                            police force, under special stipendiary magistrates, along the border
                            between Canada and the territory of the United States.</p>
                <p>Viscount Monck has also called out for permanent duty a strong force of
                            the volunteer militia, who are to be stationed on the frontier line.</p>
                <p>These measures Viscount Monck hopes will effectually prevent any such
                            attempts as those alluded to.</p>
                <closer>
                    <dateline rendition="#left">
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">British
                                    Legation</hi>, <placeName>
                            <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1864-12-26">
                            <hi rend="italic">December</hi> 26,
                                    1864</date>.</dateline>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
